sql:
SELECT f.feature_name
FROM features f
JOIN data_model_features dmf ON f.feature_id = dmf.feature_id;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM data_models 
WHERE performance_metrics > (SELECT AVG(performance_metrics) FROM data_models);

external_knowledge:
This question assumes that the importance score is a measure of how much each feature contributes to the data model's predictions or performance; 
Data models are used to make predictions or classify data based on the features used to train the model; 
Features are the input variables used to train a data model.
